{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, A is not an R-BAO.Definition 5.14 (Full Frame and Principal Frame of a V-BAO).",
    "Given a V-BAO A = ⟨A, ∧, -, ⊤, {■ i } i∈I ⟩ and algebraic model M = ⟨A, θ⟩, we define the full frame A u = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P u ⟩ of A, the principal frame A p = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P p ⟩ of A, and M p = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, π⟩ as follows:1.",
    "S = A \\ {⊥}; 2.",
    "⊑ is the restriction of ≤ to S; 3. xR i y iff for all y ′ ∈ A: if ⊥ ̸ = y ′ ⊑ y, then x ∧ ♦ i y ′ ̸ = ⊥; 4.",
    "P u = RO(S, ⊑) (recall Notation 2.19); 5."
  ]
}